    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i keep getting these intermittent \"Connection Reset by Peer\" errors on one of our ec2 instances in us-east-1. it's only happening during peak traffic hours mostly. here is a snippet from the cloudwatch logs:\n\n2023-10-27T14:22:01Z [ERROR] connection reset by peer (errno 104)\n2023-10-27T14:22:05Z [ERROR] connection reset by peer (errno 104)\n\ncould it be something with the security group or is this more likely a load balancer issue?",
