      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "thanks. i checked the cpu and it's actually pretty low, like under 40% even during the spikes. the network throughput looks fine too. i'm wondering if it's an idle timeout issue or maybe something at the OS level? what should i check to see if it's a kernel or TCP setting issue rather than just resource exhaustion?",
      "beast_suffix": "",
      "targeted_response_start_logprob": 0.0
    },
