      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If CPU and network are fine, you should start looking at the application's behavior or the operating system's TCP stack settings. Check your application logs for any specific errors that coincide with the resets, which might point to application-level timeouts. On the OS level, look into kernel parameters like `net.core.somaxconn` or TCP connection limits to see if the OS is rejecting new connections under pressure, even if CPU is low. Sometimes, an aggressive idle timeout configured by an upstream proxy or the application itself is the culprit.",
      "source": "target",
