      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay, i'll check somaxconn. but it's just so weird because it's so random. like, it's not a steady stream of errors, it's just these weird, sudden drops in connection. it feels almost like some invisible thing is just kicking the connections off whenever it feels like it. is there any scenario where an AWS component would just randomly drop packets or terminate a session without a clear resource trigger?",
